 - **Remove Unused Macros**:
Delete the macro definitions for `CHECK_OVERFLOW` and `MSB`. These macros were introduced in [this PR](https://github.com/numpy/numpy/commit/83c780d1cc1b6d2d8e609b0e62ccbe153be9148c#diff-9f2fe26e9f4272f627b48e611eb61d88665afbdcd8db501bc422b8f5d44bca8fR13), but are no longer used. While `CHECK_OVERFLOW` was indeed used in that PR, `MSB` is defined but never utilized in the codebase.
 - **Add Explicit Casting**:
To avoid implicit type casting, add explicit type casting where needed. (Such as line 109 in `string_buffer.h`.)
 - **Rename Misleading Parameter Names**:
Rename parameters that could be misleading. For example, in line 590, the parameter `n_chars` in the function `buffer_memcpy` could be misunderstood as referring to the number of characters.
 - **Add Static Assertions**:
In line 1034, within the `call_buffer_member_function` function, add a `static_assert` to ensure that undefined functions cannot be used at compile time. This addition will prevent incorrect usage of undefined member functions and provide compile-time safety.
 - **Rename Methods and Structures**:
Rename some methods and structs to make sure that they are fixed to our c style conduct. (such as line 1722)
 - **Refine Code Structures**:
On lines 1828 and 1950, move certain code inside the corresponding if branches. This will ensure that these blocks of code are not executed unnecessarily if the condition evaluates to false.
```c++
if (enc == ENCODING::UTF8) {
    traverse_buf = Buffer<enc>(buf.after, 0) - 1;
}
else {
        traverse_buf = buf + (new_stop - 1);
}
```
 - **Fix Buffer Overflow Risk**:
Set length to `0`, it seems that there is no use of length, and it may let buffer out-of-range.(line 2068)
```c++
// original code
size_t length = len1;
if (enc == ENCODING::UTF8) {
    start = buf1.after;
    length = 0;
}
else if (enc == ENCODING::UTF32) {
    start = buf1.buf + sizeof(npy_ucs4) * len1;
}
else {
    start = buf1.buf + len1;
}

Buffer<enc> end1(start, length);
```","created_at":"2024-10-25T03:47:06Z","updated_at":"2024-10-25T03:47:06Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":null,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numpy/numpy/pulls/27640/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numpy/numpy/pulls/27640/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numpy/numpy/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numpy/numpy/issues/27640/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numpy/numpy/statuses/2ac8f07de292ee2a195305f29f93b3b8a75e4cb0","head":{"label":"fengluoqiuwu:comment_string_buffer","ref":"comment_string_buffer","sha":"2ac8f07de292ee2a195305f29f93b3b8a75e4cb0","user":{"login":"fengluoqiuwu","id":163119756,"node_id":"U_kgDOCbkCjA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/163119756?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu","html_url":"https://github.com/fengluoqiuwu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fengluoqiuwu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"repo":{"id":865120503,"node_id":"R_kgDOM5Cw9w","name":"numpy","full_name":"fengluoqiuwu/numpy","private":false}},"base":{"label":"numpy:main","ref":"main","sha":"88a6a0070d9d50f034c3f31f5e1d